urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.
subtitle: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.

urlText: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked
content: If travelling by Coach to or from Bathurst you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at Bathurst station and your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station. When using Opal you will need to reserve a seat, at no cost, through the Contact Centre by calling 13 22 32 (Between 07:00 to 22:00 each day).
subtitle: Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked

urlText: Juniors Kingsford Interchange and bus roadway temporary bus stop closures
content:
From 9pm Friday 9 to 5am Monday 9 August 2021, the partial closure of the L2 and L3 lines will mean buses cannot access the Moore Park roadway and the Juniors Kingsford interchange.

The following closures will be in place:

Moore Park Roadway
-Services towards the City
  • Moore Park Busway at Lang Rd (202144) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde before Cleveland St (202112) affecting routes 373, 374, 376 and 377.
  • Moore Park Busway at Robertson Rd (202138) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde opp Robertson Rd (202111) affecting routes 373, 374, 376 and 377.
  • Moore Park Busway after Alison Rd (203348) will be closed. The alternative stop is Alison Rd before Doncaster Ave (203143) affecting routes 373, 374, 376 and 377.
-Services away from the City
  • Moore Park Busway after Lang Rd (202143) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde after Lang Rd (202128) affecting routes 373, 374, 376 and 377.
  • Moore Park Busway at Robertson Rd (202145) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde before Robertson Rd (202129) affecting routes 373, 374, 376 and 377.
  • Moore Park Busway before Alison Rd (202146) will be closed. The alternative stop is Alison Rd opp Doncaster Ave (203337) affecting routes 373, 374, 376 and 377.
Juniors Kingsford Interchange
  • Juniors Kingsford Stand A (203290) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde at Hayward St (203254) for the 400 towards Sydney Airport via Eastgardens and 400N towards Eastgardens.
  • Juniors Kingsford Stand B (203292) will be closed. The alternative stop is Anzac Pde at Wallace St (203245) for the 400 and 400N towards Bondi Junction.
subtitle: Juniors Kingsford Interchange and bus roadway temporary bus stop closures

properties.speechText: From 9 PM Friday 6 to 5 AM Monday 9 August, the partial closure of the L2 and L3 lines will mean buses cannot access the Moore Park roadway and the Juniors Kingsford interchange.
